function [m,s,llik] = nfit_data(x)% [m,s] = nfit_data(x)%    finds maximum likelihood estimates of parameters of the normal%    distribution that would account for obtaining the data in vector X.  In%    addition to mean and stdev, the function returns the log likelihood of%    obtaining the data given the optimal parameters.% This is intended as a testing ground for fancier functions.%%    See llikdata_normal.m%    M. Shadlen 9/94global DataData = x;% generate guessesq(1) = mean(x);q(2) = std(x);n = fmins('llikdata_normal',q);m = n(1);s = n(2);llik = llikdata_normal(n);